Power will be disrupted briefly in parts of the city on Monday due to annual calibration work of electrical equipment at Marapalam sub station.Power supply will be interrupted from 10 a.m. to noon in Thengaithittu, Nehru Nagar, Vasanth Nagar, Sapthagiri Nagar, Athiparasakthi Nagar and Fishing Harbour and from noon to 2 p.m. in Govinda Salai, Ilango Nagar, Sithankudi, Brindavanam, Santhi Nagar, Sarathy Nagar, Thendral Nagar, Saram, Kamaraj Salai, Udayar Thottam, Abdul Kalam Nagar, Nethaji Nagar, Vanarapet, Colas Nagar, Cuddalore Road, Mudaliarpet, Marai Malai Adigal Salai, Attupatti, Annai Indira Ninaivu Nagar and Bharathi Mill.Between 3 p.m. and 4 p.m., power supply will be disrupted on the ECR between Marapalam junction and Rajiv Gandhi Statue in areas including Ellaipillaichavady, Nellithope, Maramalai Adigal Salai, Mariamman Nagar, Jhonsy Nagar, Natesan Nagar, Anna Nagar, TV Salai, Saram, Kosapalayam, Kamaraj Salai, Thanthai Periyar Nagar, Lenin Street, Orleanpet, Periyar Nagar, Savanapet, Mullai Nagar, Karamanikuppam, Viveganandha Nagar, Victoria Nagar, Bommianpet Housing Board Quarters, Thilagar Nagar, Vanashakti Nagar, Pettaiyanchathiram, VVP Nagar, Goundanpalayam, Gandhi Nagar and Thilaspet.Power supply will also be disrupted from 4 p.m. to 5 p.m. in Velrampet, Divan Kandappa Nagar, Health Employees Colony, Thirumagal Nagar, Thulukanathamman Nagar, Kombakkam, Maraimalai Nagar, Ottampalayam, Sudhana Nagar, Murungapakkampet, Pappanchavady, Annai Theresa Nagar, Ramanar Nagar, MGR Nagar, Jayamoorti Raja Nagar and extension, PSC Bank Colony, Jothi Nagar and extension, Variyar Nagar, Divan Sathiamorthy Nagar and Ansari Duraisamy Nagar.Annual calibration of electrical equipment at Marapalamsub-stationto be taken up